Date: Mon, 23 Aug 1993 16:56:01 GMT

In article <00971714.609E9760.18815@ccs.ios.bc.ca> dzubint@ccs.ios.bc.ca (Thomas Dzubin) writes:
>I can see it now...Peter MacDonald becoming the Salmon Rushdie of the
>Internet...Running from site to site, logging in for only minutes at a
>time before jumping into the trunk of a non-descript car.  FSF hit-teams
>following closely behind.
I think not. I question the way he keeps hold of his scripts and would
argue that morally he isn't following the one true FSF path 8-). I don't
deny him the right too.
>btw: don't you just need to make the source code "available somewhere"
>under the GPL?  I don't think you have to distribute it with your package.
If you are selling the package you need to provide a coupon or clear offer
for the source code supplied at media (might be + handling) cost or provide
the source code. WHen you are not selling it you have some slightly wider
options.
>PDP-11 owner and proud of it!
TRS80 owner and proud of it!

