From: fgg@gemini.gsfc.nasa.gov (Frank G. Gomez)
Subject: drivers available ?
Date: 23 Aug 1993 19:47:35 GMT

We are trying to evaluate how suitable linux would be for a data
acquisition application that we support. If anyone could answer some
of these questions it would help:

Are there available linux drivers to support:

   Digiboard PC/8i Serial Card

   National Instruments PC-AT IEEE-488 board

   Bi-directional centronix ports

Does linux accept other drivers written to any particular standard,
say System V Release 4?

Are high resolution alarms (0.01 second resolution) available?

Is the time of day available with 0.01 second resolution? Usually clock
ticks since boot is good enough, if HZ >= 100.

We know about f2c, but is G77 suppose to be a gnu FORTRAN compiler? Is there
any idea about when this might be available?

Any help would be greatly appreciated. You can reply directly to

weh@gemini.gsfc.nasa.gov

Thanks, Ed Himwich
-- 
Frank G. Gomez  
fgg@gemini.gsfc.nasa.gov

